OL,3,CGrieving mum backs calls to seek
OL,4,Csecond opinions in hospitals
OL,6,F"It makes them part of their own care.
OL,7,FIt's not a complaints service - it's
OL,8,Ffor people to raise a clinical
OL,9,Fconcern."
OL,11,FThe service has been in place at
OL,12,FYsbyty Gwynedd for 18 months.
OL,14,FIf someone is worried a relative has
OL,15,Fdeteriorated, they can call a
OL,16,Fswitchboard and an experienced nurse
OL,17,Fwill come and assess them.
OL,19,FDoctors involved in the scheme say it
OL,20,Fshould be part of all hospital care.
